Business Brief -- Everest  Jennings International:
   Charge in Fourth Quarter
   To Result in Loss for 1991
The maker of wheelchairs and other medical equipment said
its new headquarters will be merged with those of Smith 
Davis, the company's nursing home and hospital bed
subsidiary, by late 1992.
   The company also said BIL (Far East Holdings) Ltd.,
formerly known as Industrial Equity (Pacific) Ltd. and the
company's largest shareholder, has acquired all of Everest 
Jennings's debt, a total of $22.6 million, from Security
Pacific National Bank under an agreement reached last
September.